  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>On completion of this ritual, [[/roll 1d4]] @UUID[Compendium.dnd4e.example_character.Actor.n1LXn8qhWKAwCErL]{Badgers} appear in the square occupied by the caster. The ritual does not give caster any ability to command or communicate with the summoned badgers.</p><p>The summoning process appears to put the badgers into a foul mood, which will be directed at the nearest thing to them, usually the caster. The nature check result is used to determine their reaction to summoning.</p><table><thead><tr><th style=\"width:4em\"><p>Check Result</p></th><th><p>Badger Reaction</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>Enraged: Will immediately attack the summoner.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>15-24</p></td><td><p>Grumpy: Will attack if threatened, provoked or looked at funny. Otherwise will wander off.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>25+</p></td><td><p>Annoyed: Will wander off unless attacked or provoked.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",
      "chat": "Nobody is entirely sure why this ritual was created. Probably a druidic prank.",
